  "texts": [
    "The first papers were primarily designed to provide a proof of concept, showing that AI can indeed provide support (Althoff et al., 2016; Cameron et al., 2017; Darcy et al., 2021; Ly et al., 2017; Meng & Dai, 2021; Nicol et al., 2022; Sharma et al., 2022; Wenger et al., 2025).",
    "The biggest gap, however, remains in comparing the quality of support between humans and AI, especially in realtime (Yin et al., 2024).",
    "Such comparison is important not only to determine whether AI is better or worse than humans, as language models dramatically improve every month, but more so because of what it tells us about how to improve human emotional support: whether it is driven by skill or motivation, how it is impacted by knowledge of the source of support, and whether it is dependent on the specific language being used.",
    "The goal of the current paper is to begin to answer these questions.",
    "We focus on one of the most established and highly researched strategies for emotional support, cognitive reappraisal, which the ability to reframe negative situations in a way that can contribute to the reduction of negative emotions (Gross, 1998 (Gross,, 2015;; Uusberg et al., 2019)."
  ],
